'''Bicester Village''' is an [[outlet shopping]] centre on the outskirts of [[Bicester]], a town in [[Oxfordshire]], England. It is owned by Value Retail plc.<ref>http://www.bicestervillage.com/en/shopping/brands/</ref>  The centre opened in 1995.

Most of its stores are in the [[luxury goods]] and [[designer clothing]] sector. The centre is the second most visited location in the [[United Kingdom]] by [[China|Chinese]] tourists, after [[Buckingham Palace]].<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/travel/destinations/europe/united-kingdom/articles/What-Chinese-tourists-really-like-about-Britain/</ref>

==Expansion==
On 17 April 2015 [[Cherwell District]] Council approved plans to demolish the nearby [[Tesco]] store and to construct a further 28 retail units and an extra 519 parking spaces. A new [[Park & Ride]] and major road improvements, funded by the centre's owners, were also announced.<ref name="cdcapproved">{{cite web|url=http://www.cherwell.gov.uk/index.cfm?articleid=10647|title= Green light for Bicester Village's revised expansion plans|publisher=Cherwell Valley Council|date=2015-04-17|access-date=2015-05-18}}</ref> It is hoped that this expansion will create around 3,500 new jobs in Bicester Village.<ref>{{cite news| newspaper=Bicester Advertiser |url=http://www.bicesteradvertiser.net/news/9694318.Expansion_of_Bicester_Village_and_Tesco_could_create_3_500_jobs/?ref=mr&ref=mmsp |title=Expansion of Bicester Village and Tesco could create 3500 jobs |date=9 May 2012 }}</ref>

The new stores opened on 19 October 2017. 
<ref>{{cite news| newspaper=Oxford Mail |url=http://www.oxfordmail.co.uk/news/15604697.IN_PICTURES__Bicester_Village_grand_opening/  |title=Bicester Village unveils new shops as part of expansion |date=19 October 2017 }}</ref>

==Public transport links==
The centre is served by [[Bicester Village railway station]], which has a regular direct connection to [[Marylebone station|London Marylebone]] and {{rws|Oxford}}, provided by [[Chiltern Railways]]. This station was formerly known as Bicester Town. This service is [[East West Rail|planned to be extended]]  to {{rws|Milton Keynes Central}} and {{rws|Bedford}} by 2024.

The centre is also served by the [[Stagecoach bus route X5|X5]] express coach service between [[Oxford]] and [[Cambridge]] via [[Milton Keynes]] and [[Bedford]].

